# MX Technologies
**Category:** ventures
**Domain:** fintech / open banking / data intelligence
**Website:** https://www.mx.com

## Overview
MX Technologies is a financial technology company that provides an open banking platform to banks, credit unions, and fintech developers. The platform enables secure access to financial data, data enrichment (categorization, cleaning, and normalization), account aggregation, and payment initiation through APIs. MX’s solutions help financial institutions offer personalized digital experiences, improve fraud detection, and comply with consumer data-sharing regulations such as the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau’s Section 1033 rulemaking. Founded in 2010 as MoneyDesktop, the company rebranded to MX in 2015. It is a founding member of the Financial Data Exchange (FDX), a nonprofit focused on standardizing consumer financial data access.

## Utah connection
MX Technologies is headquartered in Lehi, Utah, a prominent hub in the Silicon Slopes tech ecosystem. The company has deep roots in Utah’s fintech community and employs hundreds of people locally. It is often cited as one of the most influential private fintech companies in the state, contributing to Utah’s reputation as a center for financial technology innovation.

